      'Mexico City Stadium has been confirmed as the venue for the opening fixture of the FIFA World Cup 2026 on Thursday, 11 June 2026.\n\nHosts Mexico will open the biggest-ever edition of the World Cup with the first of 104 matches staged across 16 locations in Canada, Mexico, and the United States.\n\nThe historic venue will become the first stadium to host three FIFA World Cup opening matches, adding 2026 to its iconic roles in the 1970 and 1986 tournaments.\n\nThe full match schedule for the expanded FIFA World Cup has now been unveiled, giving the framework for a 104-game tournament featuring 48 teams across 16 host cities in three countries.\n\nMexico will have the honour of getting the tournament under way in their capital city, kicking off proceedings in a stadium that has already hosted World Cup finals and opening games.\n\nThe hosts will play all three of their group fixtures on home soil. Estadio Guadalajara will host Mexico\'s second game on Thursday, 18 June, before Mexico return to Mexico City Stadium on Wednesday, 24 June for their final group match.\n\nMexico City Stadium will also stage the Group K contest between Uzbekistan and Colombia, before hosting one match in the Round of 32 and one match in the Round of 16.\n\nFor Mexico, the opening match is more than a fixture. It is another chapter in the story of one of football\'s most iconic World Cup stages.',
